Description: Limestone ostracon: on recto and verso eight lines of administrative texts relating to work in progress in both the Valley of the Queens and the Valley of the Kings.
Curator's comments: This ostracon joins O. Petrie 30. Bibliography: J.J. Janssen, 'Gear for the Tombs', 'Revue d'Égyptologie' 43, p. 107-122; J. J. Černy and A.H. Gardiner, ‘Hieratic Ostraca’ (Oxford 1957), p.6 and pl.XIX,2; K.Kitchen, 'Ramesside Inscriptions' VII (Oxford, 1989), 333-4
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136382) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136382)
Associated places: Named in inscription: Biban el-Harim (Valley of the Queens - Thebes)
Named in inscription: Biban el-Muluk (Valley of the Kings - Thebes)
